                    <span>The Book summary on the back cover calls Chuck Zito a dying breed. Well, if that is the case, respectfuly, I say let that breed die. If you want to here about how tough Chuck Zito is and what a wonderful organization the Hells angels is, than this is the book for you. Chuck basicaly braggs about his encounters with celebreties and glorifies and justifies physical assualts on others. He also reveals that he has a distorted sense  of justice. I was hoping to find something substancial and edifying in this book, but was I was greatly disapointed. Although, the book reveals Chucks determination when facing adversity (a admirable quality) and you may be interested in hearing about certain details regarding his encounters with celebraties, his arogance and warped sense of justice arouse disgust. </span>
                  
